classical and quantum physics.

48
00:03:48,590 --> 00:03:52,080
How does classical physics deal
with the action of forces?

49
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:55,390
Particles are described as mass points.

50
00:03:55,390 --> 00:03:59,870
Their position x and
momentum p can be known with certainty.

51
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:04,600
Their motion is a smooth curve,
in space a function of time,

52
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:06,370
which we call a trajectory.

53
00:04:06,370 --> 00:04:10,114
It is determined by Newton's law,
once we know the vector

54
00:04:10,114 --> 00:04:15,190
sum of all forces acting, and the initial
conditions on the position and velocity.

55
00:04:15,190 --> 00:04:20,680
The action of forces is continuous,
thus the trajectory is a smooth curve.

56
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:22,960
The number of particles is conserved,

57
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:25,120
mass points cannot disappear or appear.

58
00:04:28,723 --> 00:04:32,630
