it allows you to drive your car.

63
00:04:47,660 --> 00:04:52,650
It's just that its validity is limited
to non-relativistic velocities and

64
00:04:52,650 --> 00:04:55,670
distances, much larger
than the size of an atom.

65
00:04:56,780 --> 00:05:00,550
To talk about subatomic
systems at high energies,

66
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:03,630
we need to go beyond classical physics.

67
00:05:05,110 --> 00:05:08,150
Quantum mechanics radically
changes the approach.

68
00:05:09,150 --> 00:05:13,850
Particles are fields described by
a probability amplitude psi, which is

69
00:05:13,850 --> 00:05:19,920
a function of the position x and the time
t, which is also called a wave function.

70
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:24,955
The square of this amplitude rho,
which must be always positive definite

71
00:05:24,955 --> 00:05:31,970
gives the probability density to find the
particle at the time t in the position x.

72
00:05:31,970 --> 00:05:34,870
This density is a probability
per unit volume.

73
00:05:34,870 --> 00:05:39,100
The trajectory does not
exist at small scales.

74
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:44,540
Multiple measurements of the position of
a particle do not form a smooth curve.

75
00:05:44,540 --> 00:05:47,570
Probability amplitude and
probability itself

76
00:05:47,570 --> 00:05:53,187
evolve starting from initial state,
described it by the Schrödinger equation.

77
00:05:54,440 --> 00:06:01,246
Particles interact with the potential,
the action the potential is continuous.

78
00:06:01,246 --> 00:06:09,825
However, the origin of
the potential remains unexplained.

79
00:06:09,825 --> 00:06:14,894
Even though the action the potential
is continuous it can be implemented

80
00:06:14,894 --> 00:06:19,570
