89
00:07:02,466 --> 00:07:05,250
its forms depends on the reference frame.

90
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:11,540
To overcome this limitation,
we have to use relativistic field theory.

91
00:07:11,540 --> 00:07:17,020
Here, we are going just to introduce
its language, its concepts and

92
00:07:17,020 --> 00:07:20,860
its results, but
we will not use it in a formal way.

93
00:07:22,110 --> 00:07:26,420
The evolution of particles is described
by a relativistic equation of motion,

94
00:07:26,420 --> 00:07:28,420
the Klein-Gordon equation,

95
00:07:28,420 --> 00:07:35,090
which is covariant because it contains
only scalars under Lorentz transformations.

96
